Background

		Mr. Ralph W. Babb Jr., has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Comerica Incorporated since October 2002 and January 2002 respectively. Mr. Babb has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Comerica Bank since October 2002 and January 2002 respectively. Mr. Babb served as the President of Comerica Incorporated and Comerica Bank since January 2002. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Comerica Incorporated from June 1995 to April 2002 and Executive ... Vice President from June 1995 to March 1999. He was responsible for Corporate Development and Planning, Controller, Treasury, Funds Management, Investor Relations, Economics, General Services and Real Estate, Corporate Legal and Corporate Staff. He joined Mercantile Bancorporation Inc. in 1978 as Controller after seven years of service with Peat Marwick Mitchell & Co., where he lastly served as an Audit Manager. He served as Treasurer of Mercantile since 1979 and Chief Financial Officer since 1983. Mr. Babb serves as a Vice Chairman of Business Leaders for Michigan. He served as Vice Chairman of Mercantile since 1987. He served as Vice Chairman of Comerica Incorporated from March 1999 to December 2001. He served as Vice Chairman for Mercantile. He has been a Director of Texas Instruments Inc. since March 15, 2010. He serves as Director of BITS Financial Services Roundtable. Since January 2004, he served as a Director of Detroit branch of Federal Reserve Bank of Chicago. He has been a Director of Comerica Incorporated since September 2001 and Comerica Bank since 2000. He served as Lead Director at Texas Instruments Inc. He serves as a Member of Federal Advisory Council at Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. He served as a Director of Tara Bankshares Corp. and its subsidiary, Tara State Bank. He served as Director of Tecumseh Products Company from 1998 to November 26, 2003. Among his professional and community affiliations, he was Board Chairman of United Way Community Services. He is a Director of Detroit Symphony Orchestra. He is a Trustee of William Beaumont Hospital. Mr. Babb holds a BS degree in Business Administration from the University of Missouri.Read Full Background




