About the Dallas FedBoards of Directors 










 Federal Advisory Council Member 
Ralph W. Babb Jr.
Chairman and CEO   Comerica Inc. and Comerica Bank   Dallas, Texas

Ralph W. Babb Jr. is chairman and CEO of Comerica Inc. and Comerica Bank. He also serves as a director of  both organizations.
Babb joined Comerica in 1995 as executive vice  president and chief financial officer. He was named a vice chairman in 1999,  responsible for a number of business units. He was named president and chief  executive officer in January 2002, completed his service as chief financial  officer in April of that year and added the title of chairman in October 2002.
Before joining Comerica, Babb served as vice  chairman for Mercantile Bancorporation Inc. in St. Louis, Missouri. He joined  Mercantile in 1978 as controller after seven years of service with Peat Marwick  Mitchell &amp; Co., where his last position was audit manager. He was named  treasurer of Mercantile in 1979, chief financial officer in 1983 and vice  chairman in 1987.
Among his professional and community affiliations,  Babb serves as a board member of the Dallas Citizens Council and the Dallas  Regional Chamber. He also serves as a board member of The Clearing House.
Babb holds a BS in business administration from  the University of Missouri. 



